Pre-Game Insights: Revitalised England to play their first Super Eights fixture against West Indies on June 19
The second round of the 2024 T20 World Cup starts on June 19 in the Caribbean islands
Defending Champions England are slotted in Group Two alongside England, West Indies and South Africa
In a fair assessment of England’s campaign so far, the current titleholders were not at their optimum best in the group stage
A washout against Scotland, followed by a 36-run defeat to arch rivals Australia, pushed them to the brink of group-stage elimination
Against Oman, they gunned down 50 off in a record 3.1 overs to turbocharge their net run rate
They went to the final group-stage match needing to win against Namibia to stay in the hunt for the second Super Eights slot
Persistent rain almost spoiled their party but in the end, they won 41 runs via the DLS method in a match reduced to 10 overs a side
Scotland's defeat against Australia cemented their place by the barest of margins
